    <text id="B0352T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Jackson receives a letter admitting Susan Berry to Howard's Grove Hospital in
                    Richmond.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau Refugees, Freedmen &amp; <abbr expan="Abandoned Lands">A.L.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="District of Virginia">Dist Va</abbr><lb/>Office Surgeon in Chief
                    <abbr expan="District">Dist</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Assistant Adjutant Surgeon">A.A. Surg</abbr>
                        D. R. Brower <abbr expan="United States Army">U.S.A.</abbr><lb/>In charge of
                        the Howard Grove Hospital, Richmond <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-12-12"><abbr expan="December">Dec</abbr> 12th 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Richmond, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>

                <p>Will receive in Hospital for treatment, when presented with this order<lb/>Susan
                    Berry<lb/>an indigent freedwoman now of Staunton <abbr expan="Virginia"
                    >Va</abbr>.</p>

                <p>Transportation to Hospital directed by <abbr expan="Brigadier General">Brig Genl</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Orlando">O.</abbr> Brown <abbr expan="Assistant Commissioner">Asst
                        Comr</abbr> Bureau &amp; to be furnished by the civil authorities.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>JJ DeLamater<lb/><abbr expan="Brevet Lieutenant Colonel">Brvt Lt Col
                            &amp; Surg in Chief</abbr><lb/>Bureau <abbr
                            expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R.F. &amp; A.L.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="District of Virginia">Dist Va</abbr></signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">
                        <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Through">Thro'</abbr> Thomas P.
                            Jackson<lb/>Agent Bureau<lb/>Staunton <abbr expan="Virginia"
                        >Va</abbr></name>
                    </seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
